cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks, specifically with training image curation and active image generation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end framework that involves machine learning and human annotation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using search engines to obtain images, which could relate to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the generation of realistic image samples, which could also relate to cs.MM (Multimedia).
